<subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-forming-quadratic-expressions-by-multiplying-2" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Forming Quadratic Expressions by Multiplying 2</title>
    <objectives component="outcomes">
        <introduction>
            <p>
            <dl>
                <li>
                    <title>Strand</title>
                    <p>
                        1.0 Numbers and Algebra
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <title>Sub-Strand</title>
                    <p>
                        1.3 Quadratic Expressions and Equations
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <title>Specific Learning Outcomes</title>
                    <p>
                        Form quadratic expressions from different situations
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li component="lesson-plan">
                    <title>Grade Level</title>
                    <p>
                        10
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li component="lesson-plan">
                    <title>Estimated Duration</title>
                    <p>
                        40 minutes
                    </p>
                </li>
            </dl>
            </p>
            <p component="lesson-plan">
                <p> Upon completion of this lesson, learners will be able to:
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <alert>Know (Conceptual Understanding):</alert> Understand the patterns that emerge when multiplying two binomials, including the square of a binomial and the difference of squares.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <alert>Do (Procedural Skill):</alert> Multiply two binomials using the distributive property (FOIL method) and simplify the resulting quadratic expression.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <alert>Apply (Application/Problem-Solving):</alert> Apply binomial multiplication to form quadratic expressions and recognize special products.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
                </p>
            </p>
        </introduction>
    </objectives>
    <axiom component="resources">
        <!-- Link to blurb -->
        <xi:include href="../../resources-blurb-lesson.ptx" />

        <sbsgroup widths="45% 45%" margins="2% 2%">
            <sidebyside>
                <p>
                    <dataurl source="lesson_plans/numbers-and-algebra/quadratic-expressions-and-equations/forming-quadratic-expressions-by-multiplying-2.pdf"> Lesson Plan </dataurl>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <dataurl source="lesson_plans/numbers-and-algebra/quadratic-expressions-and-equations/step-by-step-guide_forming-quadratic-expressions-by-multiplying-2.pdf"> Step-by-Step Guide </dataurl>
                </p>
            </sidebyside>
        </sbsgroup>
    </axiom>
    <xi:include href="../../resources-materials.ptx" />



    <paragraphs xml:id="para-multiplying-two-binomials">
        <title>Multiplying Two Binomials.</title>

        <axiom component="lesson-plan">
            <title>Problem-Solving and Discovery</title>
            <dl>
                <li>
                    <title>Suggested Time</title>
                    <p>
                        15 minutes
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <title>Objective</title>
                    <p>
                        Explore patterns in multiplying binomials through collaborative discovery.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <title>Learning Experience</title>
                    <p>
                        Groups of 3 complete a table, multiplying binomial pairs: <m>(x+2)(x+3)</m>, <m>(x+4)(x-1)</m>, <m>(x-2)(x-5)</m>, <m>(x+3)(x-3)</m>, <m>(2x+1)(x+2)</m>. After completing the table, groups discuss:
                        <ol marker="(a)">
                            <li><p>Write down results.</p></li>
                            <li><p>What is the pattern of terms when both signs are positive or both negative?</p></li>
                            <li><p>What do you notice?</p></li>
                            <li><p>How do the signs affect the result?</p></li>
                            <li><p>Create your own binomial multiplication problems.</p></li>
                        </ol>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <title>Teacher's Role</title>
                    <p>
                        The teacher circulates, asking probing questions: <q>How did you multiply the first terms?</q>, <q>What pattern do you notice with the middle terms?</q>, <q>What happens when one sign is positive and one is negative?</q>
                    </p>
                </li>
            </dl>
        </axiom>

        <activity xml:id="auto_tpa4aa8y">
            <p xml:id="auto_c6wvmoge">
                <em><term>Work in Groups</term></em>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_66nn5k4p">
                In groups of 3, look through the table below. 
                The following pairs of expressions are given. 
                Complete the table by multiplying the two binomials in the first two columns and writing the result in the third and fourth column.
            </p>
            <tabular left="medium" right="medium" top="medium" bottom="medium">
                <row>
                    <cell><m>(x + 3)</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>(x + 5)</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>(x + 3)(x + 5)</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>x^2 + 8x + 15</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><m>(y - 4)</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>(y + 2)</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>(y - 4)(y + 2)</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>y ^2 - 2y - 8</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><m>(a + 6)</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>(a - 1)</m></cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell><m>(b - 2)</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>(b + 7)</m></cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                    <cell></cell>
                </row>
            </tabular>
            <p xml:id="auto_alyugv4c">
                <ol xml:id="auto_6d14lc72" marker="(a)">
                    <li xml:id="auto_kvv574xz">
                        <p xml:id="auto_w5ntgdue">
                            After you have completed the table, 
                            discuss with your group members and write down the results in the table below.
                        </p>
                    </li>

                    <li xml:id="auto_fqb415e4">
                        <p xml:id="auto_l678yihh">
                            Discuss the pattern of the terms in the expanded form when both binomials have positive or negative terms.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_u569vd17">
                        <p xml:id="auto_lq6bn0cf">
                            What do you notice about the results?
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_l720acwk">
                        <p xml:id="auto_11whmuza">
                            How do the signs in the expressions affect the final expanded expression?
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li xml:id="auto_zbqldx6w">
                        <p xml:id="auto_1a6yce5k">
                            Can you create and expand your own binomial multiplication problems?
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </activity>

        <axiom component="lesson-plan">
            <title>Structured Instruction</title>
            <dl>
                <li>
                    <title>Suggested Time</title>
                    <p>
                        10 minutes
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <title>Objective</title>
                    <p>
                        Introduce the FOIL method and special products for multiplying binomials.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <title>Learning Experience</title>
                    <p>
                        <alert>FOIL Method:</alert> <m>(a+b)(c+d)</m>: F = <m>ac</m>, O = <m>ad</m>, I = <m>bc</m>, L = <m>bd</m>, giving <m>ac + ad + bc + bd</m>.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <alert>Special Product 1 (Perfect Square):</alert> <m>(a+b)^2 = a^2 + 2ab + b^2</m> and <m>(a-b)^2 = a^2 - 2ab + b^2</m>.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <alert>Special Product 2 (Difference of Squares):</alert> <m>(a+b)(a-b) = a^2 - b^2</m>.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <alert>Common Misconception:</alert> <q><m>(a+b)^2 \neq a^2 + b^2</m>. You MUST include the middle term <m>2ab</m>!</q>
                    </p>
                </li>
            </dl>
        </axiom>

        <investigation xml:id="auto_3atbey41">
            <p xml:id="auto_yyde2pp8">
                
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_1ierl5gc">
                What is the FOIL method, and why is it useful for multiplying binomials?
            </p>
        </investigation>

        <p xml:id="auto_03j3ymro">
            Suppose we want to Multiply
            <me>
                (a + b)(c +d)
            </me>
            We have;
        </p>

        <p xml:id="auto_35v0n2gv">
            <md>
                <mrow>(a + b)(c +d) \amp = (ac) + (ad) + (bc) + (bd)</mrow>
            </md>
        </p>

        <example xml:id="auto_bbubct43">

            <statement>
                <p xml:id="auto_vo95vmup">
                    
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_cqa76osq">
                    Find the product:
                    <me>
                        (3x - 2)(5x +8)
                    </me>                
                </p>
            </statement>

            <solution>
                <p xml:id="auto_tbrj9hmr">
                    <md>
                        <mrow>(3x) \cdot (5x) \amp = 15x^2 </mrow>
                        <mrow>(3x) \cdot(8) \amp =  24x</mrow>
                        <mrow>(-2) \cdot (5x) \amp = -10x </mrow>
                        <mrow>(-2) \cdot (8) \amp = -16</mrow>
                    </md>
                    Now combine the terms:
                    <md>
                        <mrow>15x^2 + 24x - 10x + 16 \amp = 15x^2 + 14x - 16 </mrow>
                    </md>

                    Therefore;
                    <md>
                        <mrow> (3x - 2)(5x + 8) \amp = 15x^2 + 14x - 16</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>

        <p xml:id="auto_z17u2h39">
            From the example we can see we formed an algebraic expression
        </p>

        <axiom component="lesson-plan">
            <title>Practice and Formative Assessment</title>
            <dl>
                <li>
                    <title>Suggested Time</title>
                    <p>
                        15 minutes
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <title>Objective</title>
                    <p>
                        Apply the FOIL method and special product formulas through guided and independent practice.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <title>Learning Experience</title>
                    <p>
                        <alert>Worked Example:</alert> Expand <m>(8x+5)^2</m>:
                        <md>
                            <mrow>(8x+5)^2 \amp = (8x)^2 + 2(8x)(5) + (5)^2</mrow>
                            <mrow>\amp = 64x^2 + 80x + 25</mrow>
                        </md>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <title>Teacher's Role</title>
                    <p>
                        The teacher monitors learners' work, checking for correct handling of signs and ensuring all terms are included.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </dl>
        </axiom>

        <example xml:id="auto_u6mw13r0">
            <statement>
                <p xml:id="auto_wqe9xuqh">
                    
                </p>
                <p xml:id="auto_qo2wfh0e">
                    Form a quadratic expression:
                    <me>
                        (8x + 5)^2
                    </me>                
                </p>
            </statement>

            <solution>
                <p xml:id="auto_ksp215hn">
                    <md>
                        <mrow>(8x + 5)^2 \amp = (8x + 5)(8x + 5) </mrow>
                    </md>
                    Expanding the brackets
                    <md>
                        <mrow> \amp 64x^2 + 40x + 40x + 25 </mrow>
                    </md>
                    Collect like terms and form a quadratic expression:
                    <md>
                        <mrow> \amp 64x^2 + 80x + 25 </mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>

    </paragraphs>

    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Assessment / Exit Ticket</title>
        <dl>
            <li>
                <title>Questions</title>
                <p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            <p>Form quadratic expressions:
                            <ol marker="(a)">
                                <li><p><m>2y(y+4)</m></p></li>
                                <li><p><m>3x(2x+5)</m></p></li>
                                <li><p><m>-4y(3y-2)</m></p></li>
                                <li><p><m>-3x(4x+7)</m></p></li>
                            </ol>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>Form quadratic expressions:
                            <ol marker="(a)">
                                <li><p><m>(x-1)(x-6)</m></p></li>
                                <li><p><m>(x-2)(x-3)</m></p></li>
                                <li><p><m>(2x+3)(x+4)</m></p></li>
                                <li><p><m>(3y-5)(2y+7)</m></p></li>
                                <li><p><m>(s+6)^2</m></p></li>
                            </ol>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <title>Answer Key</title>
                <p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                            <ol marker="(a)">
                                <li><p><m>2y^2 + 8y</m></p></li>
                                <li><p><m>6x^2 + 15x</m></p></li>
                                <li><p><m>-12y^2 + 8y</m></p></li>
                                <li><p><m>-12x^2 - 21x</m></p></li>
                            </ol>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                            <ol marker="(a)">
                                <li><p><m>x^2 - 7x + 6</m></p></li>
                                <li><p><m>x^2 - 5x + 6</m></p></li>
                                <li><p><m>2x^2 + 11x + 12</m></p></li>
                                <li><p><m>6y^2 + 11y - 35</m></p></li>
                                <li><p><m>s^2 + 12s + 36</m></p></li>
                            </ol>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </li>
        </dl>
    </axiom>

    <exercises xml:id="exercises-two-binomials">
        <exercise xml:id="auto_wn93903n">
            <statement>
                <p xml:id="auto_gp2c9r8j">
                    Form quadratic expressions:
                    <ol xml:id="auto_be7kj89n" marker="(a)." cols="2">
                        <li xml:id="auto_0uws52gw">
                            <m>2y(y + 4)</m>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_3z5egkeh">
                            <p xml:id="auto_tsfqdx6q">
                                <m>3x(2x+5)</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_mg4c0a4h">
                            <p xml:id="auto_ayugens8">
                                <m>-4y(3y - 2)</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_fy4rr6v2">
                            <p xml:id="auto_ppxkgqu5">
                                <m>-3x(4x + 7)</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p xml:id="auto_1m2mecek">
                    Expanding:
                    <ol marker="(a)." cols="2">
                        <li xml:id="auto_eg1d0fju">
                            <m>2y^2 + 8y</m>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_ny5wjv5i">
                            <p xml:id="auto_tmw3l9lo">
                                <m>6x^2+15x</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_371oqvxf">
                            <p xml:id="auto_aycb6tx1">
                                <m>-12y^2+8y</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_yuf4wlhz">
                            <p xml:id="auto_iqmo12oa">
                                <m>-12x^2 - 21x</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>
        <exercise xml:id="auto_znlg5mid">
            <statement>
                <p xml:id="auto_r793ra5y">
                    Form quadratic expressions:
                    <ol xml:id="auto_z35htmpk" marker="(a)." cols="2">
                        <li xml:id="auto_anmq2m8x">
                            <p xml:id="auto_z37x9pq8">
                                <m>(y + 5)(y + 2)</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_3fvq3zx9">
                            <p xml:id="auto_g64s3qv8">
                                <m>-(4 - x)(x + 4)</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_40z6qfx3">
                            <p xml:id="auto_htxq2j6w">
                                <m>(s + 6)^2</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_vyi9nymy">
                            <p xml:id="auto_blmjrksc">
                                <m>\left( \frac{1}{4} - \frac{1}{x} \right)^2</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_2bbh7vqu">
                            <p xml:id="auto_jxzyy5ui">
                                <m>(1 - 3h)(1 + 3h)</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_7yecamvp">
                            <p xml:id="auto_rqthutt4">
                                <m>(2p + 3)(2p + 2)</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_6jblnogt">
                            <p xml:id="auto_62uzaxiv">
                                <m>-10(2y^2 + 8y + 3)</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_mpg6bbeh">
                            <p xml:id="auto_710esymj">
                                <m>\left(x + \frac{4}{x} \right)^2</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p xml:id="auto_y8nkqlfp">
                    <ol marker="(a)." cols="2">
                        <li xml:id="auto_joicg29m">
                            <p xml:id="auto_1d9fsm2c">
                                Expanding:
                                <md>
                                    <mrow>(y + 5)(y+ 2) \amp = (y)(y) + (2)(y) + (5)(y) + (5)(2)</mrow>
                                    <mrow>\amp = y^2 + 7y + 10</mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_i8kljyeq">
                            <p xml:id="auto_u15okeri">
                                Expanding:
                                <md>
                                    <mrow>-(4 - x)(x + 4) \amp = -\left(4x + 16 - x^2 - 4x\right)</mrow>
                                    <mrow> \amp = -\left(-x^2 + 16\right)</mrow>
                                    <mrow> \amp = x^2 - 16</mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_7c0lywho">
                            <p xml:id="auto_s29flaqt">
                                Expanding:
                                <md>
                                    <mrow> (s + 6)^2 \amp = s^2 + (2)(s)(6) + 6^2 </mrow> 
                                    <mrow> \amp = s^2 + 12s + 36</mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_9dvc9x6a">
                            <p xml:id="auto_47fpncc8">
                                Expanding:
                                <md>
                                    <mrow> \left( \frac{1}{4} - \frac{1}{x} \right)^2 \amp = \left(\frac{1}{4}\right)^2 - \left(2\right) \left(\frac{1}{4}\right)\left(\frac{1}{x}\right) + \left(\frac{1}{x}\right)^2 </mrow> 
                                    <mrow> \amp = \frac{1}{16} - \frac{1}{2x} + \frac{1}{x^2}</mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_a48o5vzl">
                            <p xml:id="auto_z9howkll">
                                Expanding:
                                <md>
                                    <mrow> (1 - 3h)(1 + 3h) \amp = 1 + (1)(3h) + (-3h)(1) + (-3h)(3h) </mrow> 
                                    <mrow> \amp = 1 - 9h^2</mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_yh9k8w2f">
                            <p xml:id="auto_2fk8ss81">
                                Expanding:
                                <md>
                                    <mrow> (2p + 3)(2p + 2) \amp = (2p)(2p) + (2p)(2) + (3)(2p) + (3)(2) </mrow> 
                                    <mrow> \amp = 4p^2 + 10p + 6</mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_1o9n94nz">
                            <p xml:id="auto_8v4x5po1">
                                Expanding:
                                <m> -10(2y^2 + 8y + 3) = -20y^2 - 80y - 30 </m> 
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_913mllv9">
                            <p xml:id="auto_ihwams54">
                                Expanding:
                                <md>
                                    <mrow> \left(x + \frac{4}{x} \right)^2 \amp = x^2 + (2)(x)\left(\frac{4}{x}\right) + \left(\frac{4}{x}\right)^2 </mrow> 
                                    <mrow> \amp = x^2 + 8 + \frac{16}{x^2}</mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>
        
        <exercise xml:id="auto_8wob2tp8">
            <statement>
                <p xml:id="auto_rs7xg69o">
                    Form quadratic expressions:
                    <ol xml:id="auto_h3kzyi0u" cols="2">
                        <li xml:id="auto_f2m6qrwm">
                            <p xml:id="auto_kqayjvki">
                                <m>(x - 1) (x - 6) </m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_l4m78380">
                            <p xml:id="auto_isunbwq1">
                                <m>(x - 2) (x - 3)</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_forf7i2n">
                            <p xml:id="auto_l1ye1a6n">
                                <m>(2x + 3)(x + 4)</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_un0pxj2x">
                            <p xml:id="auto_0eg3nqg6">
                                <m>(3y - 5)(2y + 7)</m>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p xml:id="auto_hk9lmvg8">
                    <ol cols="2">
                        <li xml:id="auto_0lwjntbj">
                            <p xml:id="auto_k3lylmka">
                                Expanding:
                                <md>
                                    <mrow> (x - 1) (x - 6) \amp = (x)(x) + (x)(-6) + (-1)(x) + (-1)(-6) </mrow> 
                                    <mrow> \amp = x^2 - 6x - x + 6 </mrow>
                                    <mrow> \amp = x^2 - 7x + 6 </mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_w46k4930">
                            <p xml:id="auto_3ukrc8os">
                                Expanding:
                                <md>
                                    <mrow> (x - 2) (x - 3) \amp = (x)(x) + (x)(-3) + (-2)(x) + (-2)(-3) </mrow> 
                                    <mrow> \amp = x^2 - 3x - 2x +  6 </mrow>
                                    <mrow> \amp = x^2 - 5x + 6 </mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_l8ptdvgu">
                            <p xml:id="auto_7qeqay2w">
                                Expanding:
                                <md>
                                    <mrow> (2x + 3)(x + 4) \amp = (2x)(x) + (2x)(4) + (3)(x) + (3)(4) </mrow> 
                                    <mrow> \amp = 2x^2 + 8x + 3x + 12 </mrow>
                                    <mrow> \amp = 2x^2 + 11x + 12 </mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li xml:id="auto_kuyhr1da">
                            <p xml:id="auto_oz6obyz5">
                                Expanding:
                                <md>
                                    <mrow> (3y - 5)(2y + 7) \amp = (3y)(2y) + (3y)(7) + (-5)(2y) + (-5)(7) </mrow> 
                                    <mrow> \amp = 6y^2 + 21y - 10y - 35 </mrow>
                                    <mrow> \amp = 6y^2 + 11y - 35 </mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>
    </exercises>

    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Differentiation</title>
        <dl>
            <li>
                <title>Struggling Learners</title>
                <p>
                    Provide FOIL templates with labeled boxes, use color coding for each step, start with simple positive-only binomials, and pair with a supportive peer.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <title>On-Level Learners</title>
                <p>
                    Complete the core activities as described above.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <title>Advanced Learners</title>
                <p>
                    <ol>
                        <li><p>Expand <m>(2x+3y)^2</m> and <m>(3a-2b)(3a+2b)</m>.</p></li>
                        <li><p>Find <m>(x+1)(x+2)(x+3)</m>.</p></li>
                        <li><p>Create a real-world area problem that involves multiplying binomials.</p></li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <title>Extension Solutions</title>
                <p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            <p><m>(2x+3y)^2 = 4x^2 + 12xy + 9y^2</m> and <m>(3a-2b)(3a+2b) = 9a^2 - 4b^2</m>.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p><m>(x+1)(x+2)(x+3)</m>: First, <m>(x+1)(x+2) = x^2 + 3x + 2</m>. Then, <m>(x^2+3x+2)(x+3) = x^3 + 6x^2 + 11x + 6</m>.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </li>
        </dl>
    </axiom>
    <xi:include href="../../resources-assessment.ptx" />
    <xi:include href="../../resources-reflection.ptx"/>

</subsubsection>